about.description: treelib is a simple tree data structure implementation in Python.
about.summary: A Python 2/3 implementation of tree structure.

name: treelib
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "treelib" %}
{% set version = "1.5.5" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 44695f7048b0bd82b45a4fe976611f9fb52902506249d84db255976a5e8738e0

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install --no-deps . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - treelib

about:
  home: https://github.com/caesar0301/treelib
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_family: Apache
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'A Python 2/3 implementation of tree structure.'

  description: |
    treelib is a simple tree data structure implementation in Python.
  doc_url: https://treelib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/
  dev_url: https://github.com/caesar0301/treelib

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - shcheklein
    - efiop
    - MaxRis
